    <note>Xing(1) Shu [7106] He was a follower of the scholarship of Cheng(1) Hao [3102] and studied with Cheng(1) Yi [3105]. Di(2) Ruwen's [8128] father-in-law. Possibly an ancestor of Zeng(1) Ji's [1692] grandson-in-law, Xing(1) Shicai [3372]. Xing(1) Chun [3371], the son-in-law of Yin(2) Zhu's [7104] (qv.) grandnephew, Yin(2) Shun [4125], was probably a son. Yin(2) Shun also studied with Cheng(1) Yi. After studying with the Cheng brothers, he became a client of Sima Guang. When Sima Guang fell, he became attched to Zhang Dun and then turned on Dun and became a confidant of Cai Jing. CBD, 2, 1069-70.</note>
